{"build_type":"library","description":"lstat (syscall 6 — does not follow symlinks) the file at path into a shared module-global stat buffer g_statbuf, returning the syscall result (0 = ok, negative = error). The 160-byte buffer is allocated ONCE and reused for every call (the bump arena never frees, so a per-call buffer would grow ~one per entry across a recursive walk). Callers read fields from g_statbuf by offset/8 index: st_mode @ index 3, st_size @ index 6, st_mtime @ index 11. One lstat fills all fields, so callers needing several read them from one call rather than lstat-ing per field. Reuses allocate_bytes_from_mmap_arena.","module_name":"query-symlink-metadata-filling-buffer","package_name":"query-symlink-metadata-filling-buffer","module_globals":[{"global_name":"g_statbuf","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"}],"function_definitions":{"query-symlink-metadata-filling-buffer":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"path","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"statbuf_size","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":160},{"instruction_type":"global_read","dest":"buf","name":"g_statbuf"},{"instruction_type":"conditional_branch","condition_type":"numeric_compare","operator":"==","lhs":{"value":"buf"},"rhs":{"value":"zero"},"branch_on_success":[{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"allocate-character-buffer-inside-memory-arena","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"statbuf_size"}],"result_assignment_variable":"buf","result_type":"i64"},{"instruction_type":"global_write","name":"g_statbuf","value":"buf"}],"branch_on_failure":[]},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"query-symlink-metadata-filling-status-buffer","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"path"},{"kind":"var","value":"buf"}],"result_assignment_variable":"rc","result_type":"i64"},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"rc"}}]}}}